e-and-education/science-recipes/reaction-time" class=3D"sc-f9178328-0 iCaRz=
c">well-known experiment known as the "ruler drop test".</a> You'll need th=
e assistance of a family member or friend for this one, as well as a ruler:=
</p><p class=3D"sc-9a00e533-0 eZyhnA">=E2=80=A2 Sit in a chair, resting you=
r arm on a table so that your wrist is hanging off the edge, with your thum=
b and forefingers facing up.</p><p class=3D"sc-9a00e533-0 eZyhnA">=E2=80=A2=
 Ask your partner to hold a ruler vertically, over your hand, with the "zer=
o", where the numbers start, aligned with your thumb.</p><p class=3D"sc-9a0=
0e533-0 eZyhnA">=E2=80=A2 Without warning, your partner should drop the rul=
er, while you try to catch it as quickly as possible.</p><p class=3D"sc-9a0=
0e533-0 eZyhnA">=E2=80=A2 The distance the ruler falls before being caught =
is an assessment of your reaction time.</p><p class=3D"sc-9a00e533-0 eZyhnA=
">Broadly speaking, <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.g=
ov/articles/PMC4207053/" class=3D"sc-f9178328-0 iCaRzc">an excellent perfor=
mance equates</a> to catching the ruler at a distance less than 7.5cm, abov=
e average counts as 7.5-15.9cm, average is 15.9-20.4cm, while below average=
 is anything over 20.4cm and poor is more than 28cm.</p><p class=3D"sc-9a00=
e533-0 eZyhnA">Population studies have noticed a correlation between the sp=
eed of decline in reaction times and risk of <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"h=
ttps://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3906008" class=3D"sc-f9178328-0 iCa=
Rzc">multiple age-related illnesses</a>. In addition to a person's overall =
risk of death =E2=80=93 one study found that there was a significant link b=
etween a person's reaction times and the likelihood of death from <a target=
=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30100646/" class=3D"sc-=
f9178328-0 iCaRzc">all major causes</a> =E2=80=93 there is also a strong re=
lationship between this metric and the risk of death from specific conditio=
ns. This includes <a target=3D"_blank" href=3D"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov=
/articles/PMC3906008" class=3D"sc-f9178328-0 iCaRzc">coronary heart disease=
, stroke and respiratory disease</a>.</p><figure class=3D"sc-bc40c3a0-0 kXc=
vpr"><div data-testid=3D"image" class=3D"sc-5340b511-1 jJmNMc"><img src=3D"=
